(39235, 96441, 0, 1, '野花', '野花的生命力，就像我們追求我們的夢想一樣，屹立不搖。\r\nI knew that I will not lose to anybody', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2000, 0, 1, 7, 'I knew that I will not lose to anybody(我知道自己不會輸給任何人)\r\n\r\n拋棄 塗抹的面孔 尋找自己的天空\r\n劃破 墜落的煙火 是否沉睡已久\r\n撐開 疲憊的眼眸 回想寄居的承諾\r\n啟動 失落的按鈕 掙脫束縛的蛹\r\n\r\n我 眼中的沙漠 颳起一陣暴風\r\n你 是否遺忘了 曾埋藏心中的夢\r\n\r\n野花 從不向現實的世界 低頭\r\n就算 在那狂風暴雨之中 顫抖\r\n還是 要繼續堅持未完成 的夢\r\n沒有 任何的挫折能夠阻擋我', '', 313, '', 'Newman', 'Newman', '', '', '', 0, 0, 1, '2011-09-29 08:28:21', '2013-10-07 17:19:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(39236, 118740, 3690, 1, 'People Have a Little Earth', '全曲試聽，請至www.gordonsgodown.bandcamp.com \r\n', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2011, 15, 0, 7, 'reader, singer: Gordon Tseng and his daughter Sharon Tseng\r\n\r\nPoliticians are keeping themselves in power as they were.\r\nInvestors and workers are making money from their hard work.\r\nEverybody wins something he thinks he should deserve.\r\nIn the game of development the only loser is the earth.\r\n\r\nAbout what we are now doing to the earth,\r\nThe future generations don’t have any chance to say a word.\r\nWith the legacy of technology they might find solutions that work,\r\nOnly if their parents have not yet been buried by wreckage or dirt.\r\n\r\nPeople have a little Earth,\r\nWhose health gets worse and worse.\r\nShe’s been weeping to make them alert.\r\nBut, how many of them have clearly heard?\r\n', '', 285, '', 'Gordon Tseng (compose), Jeffrey Chu (arrange)', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2011-09-29 10:23:59', '2015-03-12 13:48:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(39237, 118740, 3690, 2, 'Watching Stars', 'reader: Gordon Tseng', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2011, 15, 0, 7, 'I watch the stars, so far and so white,\r\nShining on my soul longing for a flight.\r\nYour young smile, so pure and so bright.\r\nA shooting star has flashed across the good old night.\r\n\r\nLife goes on, like a canoe boat so light,\r\nUp or down, fun or fight.\r\nWhere is my paradise harbor’s eternal site?\r\nOh, is my dream but a distant kite?\r\n\r\nJust let the wind blowing yesterday gone like a sigh\r\nAnd wait for another beautiful sunrise \r\nTo start a new journey with the warm light.\r\nFeel me by watching the cloud sail in the blue sky.\r\n', '', 211, '', 'Gordon Tseng (compose), Jeffrey Chu (arrange)', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2011-09-29 10:40:46', '2015-03-12 13:48:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
