(39239, 118740, 3690, 3, 'Dad''s Tung Blossoms', 'reader: Gordon Tseng', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2011, 15, 0, 7, 'Up the hill, the Tung blossoms of this year are awake,\r\nAbove the green ocean, flying their white snowflakes.\r\nUp dad’s head hill, some of them just cannot wait\r\nTo quietly spread their snowflakes in the black night that’s not really late.\r\n\r\nDad takes us up to the hill’s peaceful lake\r\nTo feel those gentle flakes the breezes gently make.\r\nAnd, he says that just like the Tung blossoms in May,    \r\nThe bloom of youth brightens the whole life hill, on those adventure days.\r\n\r\nUp the hill, the Tung blossoms of this year have gone away.\r\nNo more white flakes flying above the green ocean or lake.\r\nBut, those on my dear dad’s head hill are still awake.\r\nOh, why are they keeping awake in that black night that’s not really late? \r\n', '', 306, '', 'Gordon Tseng (compose), Jeffrey Chu (arrange)', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2011-09-29 11:03:33', '2015-03-12 13:48:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(39240, 118740, 3690, 4, 'Island Dream', 'reader and singer: Gordon Tseng', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2011, 15, 0, 7, 'When the rockers’ first scream from Kending blues the spring,\r\nI’m taking you on our journey for the song only the Pacific Ocean can sing. \r\nWhen the Tung blossoms’ first snowflake from green mountains lights up the summer,\r\nI’m taking you by train to swim in the music by Gonliao festival lovers.\r\n\r\nA song doesn’t have to be cute.   \r\nA dream doesn’t have to be new.\r\nAn island doesn’t have to be huge\r\nAs long as I have you.\r\n\r\nWhen the first firework brightens the Danshui River in the autumn night,\r\nI’m taking you to visit the poor legendary couple twinkling up above the sky. \r\nWhen the first birds flock from Siberia flashes across the strait in the early winter,\r\nI’m taking you home and warming again the adventurous dreams that still linger. \r\n', '', 213, '', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2011-09-29 11:18:35', '2015-03-12 13:48:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(39241, 118740, 3690, 5, 'Kids and Parents', 'reader: Gordon Tseng', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2011, 15, 0, 7, 'Kids\r\n\r\nYou feel like crying when kids are able to raise their voice high\r\nTo call you mummy, daddy, and then to say ‘Hi’.\r\nYou feel like smiling when they first use their teeth to bite a pie\r\nOr when they first watch the Milky Way and curiously ask you why. \r\n\r\nParents\r\n\r\nParents feel like crying when you first open your newborn eyes\r\nEager to catch, through your tears, the first glimpse of the blue sky.\r\nThey feel like smiling when they last remember your warm lie\r\nSaying with hope that they are fine and will not die.\r\n\r\n', '', 169, '', 'Gordon Tseng, Sharon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2011-09-29 11:32:22', '2015-03-12 13:48:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(39242, 118740, 3690, 6, 'Grandpa''s Hand', 'singer: Gordon Tseng', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2011, 15, 0, 7, 'My grandpa cleaned my painted hands when I was five years old.\r\nNow, I clean his dirty hands after he fell down and no one was told.\r\nHe can’t remember the fireplace in our old house already been sold.\r\nBut, I can still feel his big warm hand when the weather is getting cold.\r\n', '', 240, '', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2011-09-29 11:50:16', '2015-03-12 13:48:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(39243, 118740, 3690, 7, 'Snow and Maple', 'singer: Sharon Tseng', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2011, 15, 0, 7, 'Though, knowing the autumn’s red rain has always been its beautiful label,\r\nThe snow just can’t wait to dance from heaven and gently touch the maple,\r\nBecause after the north wind gets strong enough to wipe off the season,   \r\nAll the cross-times love stories will freeze to but a white fable.\r\n  \r\n', '', 199, '', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2011-09-29 12:06:30', '2015-03-12 13:48:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(39244, 118740, 0, 8, 'So-called Success', 'reader, singer: Gordon Tseng', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2011, 10, 2, 7, 'Fish would think those are winners who swim fast.\r\nLions may insist those are losers who run last.\r\nIt’s ridiculous to mold yourself into their value cast\r\nIf you are a bird who can only fly to get your lifetime pleasantly passed.', '', 271, '', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2011-09-29 12:26:25', '2015-03-12 13:48:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
