(39248, 118740, 3690, 10, 'When Icebergs Are Gone', 'singer and reader: Gordon Tseng', '2011-09-29 00:00:00', 2011, 15, 0, 7, 'Please Give Them Back\r\n\r\nPlease give the land back to nature,\r\nTo the angry mountain and the fuzzy river!\r\nPlease give the forest back to the future!\r\nFrom deep wounds, it takes time to recover.\r\n\r\nWhen Icebergs Are Gone\r\n\r\nWhen icebergs are gone, the polar bear can land nowhere.\r\nSome scientists may warn you’d better not live downstairs.\r\nThrough all these years, the Lord has already seen how humans dare.\r\nAnd, when the day comes, He may keep quiet on His chair,\r\nWatching what kind of suit this smart being can invent and wear.\r\nWe all may eventually know whether Mother Nature is never unfair \r\nAnd whether, as they always say, life is short and love is rare. \r\nWhen the coldest water comes, who can have the hottest music to share?\r\n', '', 223, '', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', 'Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2011-09-29 13:02:20', '2015-03-12 13:48:43', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
